          <avActivityComment>During the day: In particular in steep rocky terrain and on sunny slopes small and medium-sized moist avalanches are possible as a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation. &lt;br/&gt; Especially adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls: The fresh snow of Sunday as well as the mostly small wind slabs can be released by a single winter sport participant above the tree line. This applies in particular on very steep slopes. &lt;br/&gt; Backcountry touring calls for caution.</avActivityComment>
